Description of pupa . Male (
Fig. 3
). Length 38.3 mm . Width at pronotum 18.6 mm . Body shape elongate, oval, stout. Color dark reddish orange. Entire body covered with fine, velvety-gold vestiture.

Distribution .
Podischnus agenor
is distributed from México to Ecuador ( Endrödi 1976 , 1985 ;
Ratcliffe 2003
). This species is found in Colombia in forest areas from the sea level to 1600 m .
